node.title: Queenslanders will be able to ditch masks once vaccination rate hits 80 per cent first dose
node.description: Premier Annastacia Palaszczuk has announced masks will no longer be required when 80 per cent of eligible Queenslanders over 16 years of age have received at least one dose of a COVID-19 vaccine.

node.title: New Yorkshire cricket chairman apologies to Rafiq, promises change
node.description: New Yorkshire Cricket Club chairman Kamlesh Patel has apologised to former player Azeem Rafiq over the county's handling of his racism allegations.

node.title: Costly tests may deter Canadians from making quick trips to the U.S.
node.description: Canada requires travelers to present the results of an expensive Covid test to enter, deterring short hops across the border.

node.title: Plan to tackle rising demand for dementia support on cards
node.description: About 70,000 New Zealanders have dementia, but that number is expected to grow to about 170,000 within the next 30 years.

node.title: COVID-19 is biggest cop killer, yet many cops resist vaccines
node.description: More than 500 law enforcement officers have died after contracting the coronavirus, making it their biggest on-the-job risk.

node.title: Jack Ciattarelli isn't conceding New Jersey governor's race yet
node.description: Democratic Governor Phil Murphy currently leads by 2.6%, over 65,000 votes.

node.title: Ancient Roman Statue Heads of Aphrodite and Dionysus Discovered in Turkey
node.description: "The findings suggest that there may have been a sculpture workshop in the region," said excavation coordinator Gokhan Coskun.

node.title: Protesters Rally in Fight Against Los Angeles Vaccine Mandate for First Responders
node.description: Freddy Escobar, president of the local firefighters union, said last week the vaccine mandate could have a "devastating impact" on the city's public safety.

node.title: Travis Scott says he'll cover funeral expenses for Astroworld victims
node.description: Scott, who was performing at the time of the surge, is facing multiple lawsuits.

node.title: Missing Girl Is Rescued After Using Hand Signal From TikTok
node.description: The girl flashed the hand signal from a car on a Kentucky interstate, the authorities said. It was created as a way for people to indicate that they are at risk of abuse and need help.

node.title: On Chicago’s West Side, Urgent Needs Collide With Washington Compromises
node.description: Activists say the needs of struggling communities in Chicago and elsewhere vastly exceed the billions Congress is spending.

node.title: Iran Fires Missiles, Torpedoes, Drones in War Games After U.S. Weapons Test in Persian Gulf
node.description: Major General Gholam-Ali Rashid said Iranian forces "will crush any threat posed by any arrogant and aggressive power, at any level, and originating from any territory."
